cis/Book
	Directory holding fine information about the reported crime in a particular
	police station, among informations held includes Information about the accused
	personnel, action taken against the reported offense, any arrests made, details
	of the reported crime and personal information of the personnel reporting the
	crime.

cis/Core
	Directory express informations on priviledges and authorities of system users
	and the range of tasks the can perform which may range from just viewing data
	posting data, to generating reports from the crime data.

	Makes use of django Users to control priviledges, and zones the personnel
	belongs to.
	
	Suggested alternative name for this application is Control, to make it 
	more descriptive.

cis/Investigation
	This directory holds information recorded in an investigation book related to
	the reported crime, indeed if the reported crime had an opened case that
	initiated an investigation, it holds Investigation register number, RB
	Number of the case being investigated, complainant name, offenses investigated
	the name of detective investigating.
	
	It also contains an evidence file containing minute sheets, charges, details of
	the acccused, name of the investigation officer, total value of properties and
	criminal case number.

cis/Locations
	This directory holds details of locations police stations distributed country wide
	categorized from country, to region, district down to ward level. holding particulars
	about the police station.

cis/Offenses
	This directory holds details about the recorded offenses from variety of police
	stations country wide, and categorizes the according to current format. which
	includes Major/Minor offenses and type of offense, whether civil, criminal or
	of any other kind.

cis/Personal
	This directory holds full details of personnel information including all particulars
	such as person's name, age, sex, nationality/tribe, occupation, postal address
	and suggested phone number, e-mail, voter's id number to cope with technology
	and the report book associated with the person who's information is detailed.


cis/templates/
	Django admin tempaletes

cis/application_name/templates/
	All the application templates should be in the it's application folder under templates
	for each project, there needs to be templates unique to managing the templates for the main content portions.
	within the confines of the application you're working in, you can make templates local and relative to the application you create.

